              Dates and Time
--------------------------------------------
python date is a module we can import name as datetime to work with date and Objects
==> The date conatain year,month,day,hour,min,sec and Microseconds
==> the date time module has many methods to return information about the date object


creating date Object
-----------------------

--> to create a date, we can use the datetime() class of the datetime Module
--> the datetime()  requires three parameters to create a date: year , Month, day

import datetime

x = datetime.datetime(2022,10,21)
print(x)



           strftime                   --> String from time
---------------------------------

--> the datetime object has a method for formatting date objects into readable strings
--> the method is called strftime(), and take one parameter ,
format to specify the format of the String

import datetime

x = datetime.datetime(2022,10,21)
print(x.strftime("%A")   ==> friday
print(x.strftime("%B")   ==> OCTOBER



